Knowing multiple languages, especially the languages used in developing countries, can give children a better chance of finding good jobs in the future.
In Scotland, each school is different in terms of the language in which they teach.
Many schools focus on the classical modern languages, while others teach languages classified as important in the UK when looking forward to 2020, such as Mandarin and Japanese.
No matter what your child is interested in, there will always be a multitude of languages to choose from in independent schools, and teachers who are specialists in this area.
Scottish independent schools are dedicated and want to create a learning environment that will prepare children and provide the properties they need to close, no matter what the future brings.
One cannot reject that in this global, business-oriented environment, languages are vital to the future of the country, so this must be reflected in the education sector.
Modern languages should be called "international communication properties."
Independent schools will continue to offer this choice, thus offering diversity and high expertise to Scotland's young people.
